## Remarks  
 When you set the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Interval%2A> property to a value of zero (0.0), one strip line will be displayed, with a width specified by the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.StripWidth%2A> property. When you set <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Interval%2A> to a value of other than zero, multiple strip lines will be shown. The unit that is used for the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Interval%2A> property is defined by the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.IntervalType%2A> property.  



